  <p> <h1 style="color:#222222; background:#FFFFFF;">
  Tanker ships are classified into several tanker ship types:
  <li><u>Oil Tankers-</u> Ships that transport oil.</li>
  <li><u>Chemical and Product Carrier-</u> Ships that carried liquid chemical and others liquid product. </li>
  <li><u>Liquefied Gas Carrier-</u> Ships that transport liquified gas, such as LPG and LNG</li>
  <li><u>Others-</u> These Tankers transport wine,juices, integrated tug barges, and other commodoties.</li>
 
  Tankers are also categorized according to their sizes:
   <li><u>Capesize  </u></li>
   <li><u>Suezmax</u></li>
   <li><u>ULCC </u></li>
   <li><u>VLCC </u></li>
   <li><u>Handy </u></li>
   <li><u>Lighter </u></li>
   <li><u>Handymax </u></li>
   <li><u>Aframax </u></li>
   <li><u>Panamax </u></li>
    </h1> </p> 
	
